&lt;a href="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/idCqTPQ4eQU6bqY-3O6Bd9T5HPk/1/da"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/idCqTPQ4eQU6bqY-3O6Bd9T5HPk/1/di" border="0" ismap="true"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;This is just to let you know that the &lt;a href="http://www.ukadi.co.uk/2010/11/theory-test-changes-questions-and.html"&gt;theory test does not change today 1st september 2011&lt;/a&gt;, though sometime later in the month, the DSA will be publishing new theory test study materials for those who will be taking the theory test from Monday 23rd January 2012.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you don't already know, then from January 23rd 2012, the theory test will be based on questions and answers that will not have been avaialble to the public via publications or the various licenced websites on the internet, this basically means that you need to have studied and understood the highway code to correctly answer the quetions.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;So if you plan to take and pass your theory examination before 31st december 2011, you can continue to use the current study materials available, however if you dont reach the &lt;a href="http://www.ukadi.co.uk/2010/11/should-driving-age-be-17.html"&gt;driving age of 17&lt;/a&gt; till then or your commitments will not allow you to take the test till the new year, then you should wait till the &lt;a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/product/0115531963/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=ukdrscpathdrt-21&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1634&amp;creative=19450&amp;creativeASIN=0115531963" rel="nofollow"&gt;new Books/CD Roms/DVDs are released later in the year by the DSA&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/product/0115531963/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=ukdrscpathdrt-21&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1634&amp;creative=19450&amp;creativeASIN=0115531963" rel="nofollow" target="tiwo"&gt;&lt;img style="cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 300px; height: 300px;" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-2O0VXpmcXUs/TePXpmQVVmI/AAAAAAAAAAw/_nyFYl-JE1g/s400/TheoryTest2011.jpg" border="0" alt=""id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5612566670277432930" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;My top advice for anyone who wants to pass the UK driving test of which the theory is the first phase is to thoroughly go through the &lt;a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/product/0115528148/ref=as_li_tf_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=ukadi-driving-test-control-post-21&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=1634&amp;creative=6738&amp;creativeASIN=0115528148" rel="nofollow" target="frwii"&gt;UK Highway code&lt;/a&gt;, as most of the informtion you need is there, but more importantly it will make you a safer and more confident driver when out on the road.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you require high quality &lt;a href="http://www.ukadi.co.uk"&gt;driving lessons&lt;/a&gt; from a very helpful, patient and fully qualified instructor, then why not call or send me a text message on &lt;b&gt;07956233032&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Subscribe to my Driving Test Tips so you don't miss any future articles and get DSA updates direct to your inbox by &lt;a href="http://www.feedburner.com/fb/a/emailverifySubmit?feedId=302913&amp;amp;loc=en_US"&gt;Email&lt;/a&gt;. The service is provided and powered by Google Feedburner, so I don't personally keep your email addresses, and you can remove yourself anytime after passing the driving test with just one mouse click, you can also follow &lt;a href="http://twitter.com/ukadi_"&gt;UKADI on twitter&lt;/a&gt; or join my &lt;a href="http://www.facebook.com/UKADI"&gt;UKADI Facebook&lt;/a&gt; page.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;Additional test advice&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.ukadi.co.uk/2011/06/11-theory-test-centres-close-august.html"&gt;Theory test centres closing&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.ukadi.co.uk/2011/04/lost-theory-test-can-i-take-driving.html"&gt;Lost theory test certificate, can I take 